# R - Rules
## We will follow incremental delivery approach - develop one small acceptance criterial at a time, get it completely done before moving to the next one.

## We will follow Behavior Driven Development and Acceptance Test Driven Development strictly
### All requirement will be put into *_req.txt
#### "*" could be the compoment or feature name, e.g., MacClient_req.txt, user_req.txt, prompts_req.txt, Chat_req.txt etc
#### The structure of the *_req.txt:
{
	# Feature (defines high level requirement)
	## User Story (defines detailed requirement)
	### Acceptance Criterial (defines application behaviors)
}
#### When I provide requirement, automatically add User Stories and Acceptance Criterials for that requirement, and add them into req.txt
#### I put the prompt of generating user stories and acceptance criterials into file atdd.prompt.
#### Always keep *_req.txt up-to-date

### Always add User Stories and Acceptance Criterials before starting development a new feature
### Always add automated UI tests and Unit Tests before changing code

## We will follow Test Driven Development strictly
### Before code, add automated tests first
### Code to pass the test and meet the requirement
### Do code refactory
### Run regression test to ensure the new code is not affecting other features

## We want technical excellence in architecture design. 
### When you think of code design or solution, always prioritize good design patterns, best practices
### Do code review often, suggest code refactory whenever possible
### Always run regression test and ensure 100% passrate after the code is completed.

## We want high quality code. 
### Always add enough error handling, always add enough prints in terminal to help diagnose issues
### Be very careful when usign system resources like pointers, memory, capturing system behaviors like keyboard input, shortcut triggers etc

## A new feature will be considered as done when the Definition of Done defined in DoD.txt is met

## pre-defined commands:
